    dc:date "2018" ;
    dc:title "A new species of Leptolalax (Anura: Megophryidae) from Son Tra Peninsula, central Vietnam" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1187781>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1187783>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1187785>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1187787>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1187789> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1187781>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Holotype of Leptolalax rowleyae sp. nov. in preservative (A–E) and in life (F,G), respectively. A–C, dorsal, ventral, and lateral views of body; D, volar view of right hand; E, thenar view of right foot; F, dorsolateral view; G, ventral view. Note: the semicircle seen in the eye of frog in F is from a ring flash and not a natural coloration. Photos by Luan T. Nguyen." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1187781/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1187783>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Paratypes of Leptolalax rowleyae sp. nov. in life. A, male ITBCZ 2782 in situ; B, male ITBCZ 2798; C, calling male ITBCZ 2786 in situ (shows comparatively large single subgular vocal sac inflated); D, juvenile IBTCZ 4472; E and F, dorsolateraland ventral views of female ITBCZ 4471. Note:the semicircle seen in the eye of frog in D is from a ring flash and not a natural coloration.Photos by Luan T.Nguyen." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1187783/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1187785>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Advertisement call of Leptolalax rowleyae sp. nov. A, B, a 15 s waveform of relative amplitude (Rel. amp.) of holotype ITBCZ 2783 (recorded at ambient air temperature of 20.8 o C) and of an un-vouchered individual (recorded at ambient air temperature 21°C); power spectrum (relative amplitude vs. frequency) of a call (C); expanded 0.4 s waveform of relative amplitude (D) and corresponding spectrogram (E) of a call of holotype ITBCZ 2783; expanded 0.4 s waveform of relative amplitude (F) and corresponding spectrogram (G)of a call of an un-vouchered individual (same as inB)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1187785/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1187787>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Tadpole of Leptolalax rowleyae sp. nov. (ITBCZ 2790, stage 38). A–C, lateral, dorsal and ventral views, in life (photos by Luan T. Nguyen); D, schematic drawing of the oral disc in preservative; E, keratodonts of first posterior tooth row (P1) (drawn and photo by Dung T.Le)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1187787/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1187789>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Typical breeding habitat of Leptolalax rowleyae sp. nov. in the type locality: Son Tra Nature Reserve, Son Tra Peninsula, Da Nang City, Vietnam.Frogs were recorded along the cascade stream. Photo by Luan T.Nguyen." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1187789/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

